# Agentic AI Bug Hunter

## Overview

Agentic AI Bug Hunter is a multi-agent AI system designed to automatically analyze source code, detect potential bugs, and generate structured vulnerability reports using Large Language Models (LLMs).

This project demonstrates how Agentic AI architecture can be applied to automated code review and cybersecurity analysis.

---

## Objective

The primary objective of this project is to:

* Automatically detect bugs and vulnerabilities in source code
* Implement a multi-agent AI workflow
* Use LLM reasoning for intelligent bug analysis
* Generate structured and exportable reports

---

## System Architecture

The system follows an Agent-based workflow:

Input Code / Documents
→ Retriever Agent
→ Analyzer Agent
→ LLM Reasoning
→ Structured Bug Report (CSV)

### Retriever Agent

* Retrieves relevant context from documents
* Improves reasoning by providing structured input to the analyzer

### Analyzer Agent

* Analyzes code logic
* Detects potential bugs and vulnerabilities
* Generates structured findings

### LLM Integration

* Provides intelligent reasoning
* Generates explanations and suggested fixes
* Assigns severity levels

---

## Project Structure

AGENTIC-AI-BUGDETECTOR/

agents/              - Contains Analyzer and Retriever agents
documents/           - Input code or logs for analysis
server/              - Backend/API logic (if applicable)
main.py              - Main execution file
output.csv           - Generated bug report
requirements.txt     - Python dependencies
.env                 - Environment variables
README.md            - Project documentation

---

## Tech Stack

* Python
* Large Language Models (LLMs)
* Pandas
* python-dotenv
* Flask / FastAPI (if server used)
* CSV Reporting

---

## Installation

### 1. Clone the Repository

git clone https://github.com/your-username/agentic-ai-bug-detector.git
cd agentic-ai-bug-detector

### 2. Create Virtual Environment

python -m venv venv

Activate:

Windows:
venv\Scripts\activate

Mac/Linux:
source venv/bin/activate

### 3. Install Dependencies

pip install -r requirements.txt

### 4. Add Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file and add:

OPENAI_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

---

## Running the Project

python main.py

The system will:

* Load input documents
* Execute Retriever Agent
* Execute Analyzer Agent
* Generate structured bug report
* Save results to output.csv

---

## Output Format

The generated CSV report typically includes:

* File Name
* Line Number
* Bug Type
* Severity
* Description
* Suggested Fix
* Confidence Score

